  "text": "The theory of strategic niche management, instead, described a market niche as juxtaposed to the mainstream market [CITATION_1] and the socio-technological regime (Raven, 2006) . Niches attempt to resolve the conflicts and intrinsic problems of the socio-technological regime and can eventually reshape or replace it [CITATION_2] . Nevertheless, their small scale and geographically limited focus may hamper the transmission of radical innovation to the mainstream market [CITATION_3] .",
